Language: en

00:00:11.350 --> 00:00:17.440
This is William Clark Gable, one of the

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:20.350
most successful Hollywood leading men

00:00:20.350 --> 00:00:21.520
ever

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:25.630
and one of the most unlikel, his ears

00:00:25.630 --> 00:00:28.180
were too big and stuck out there were

00:00:28.180 --> 00:00:31.360
gaps between his teeth and his voice was

00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:35.739
high and loud. Clark Gable was born Feb.

00:00:35.739 --> 00:00:39.730
1st, 1901 in Cades Ohio.  He was the

00:00:39.730 --> 00:00:40.230
only child of William Henry Gable &amp;

00:00:40.230 --> 00:00:46.180
Adaline Hirschmann Gable.  Clark's

00:00:46.180 --> 00:00:48.190
father was an experienced oil well

00:00:48.190 --> 00:00:51.010
driller,  his mother Adaline was a

00:00:51.010 --> 00:00:54.040
housewife that unfortunately passed away

00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:58.120
when Clark was only 10 months old. She

00:00:58.120 --> 00:01:01.330
died on a fourteenth of november 1901

00:01:01.330 --> 00:01:05.170
believed from a seizure that was probably

00:01:05.170 --> 00:01:09.520
caused from a brain tumor. Clark was sent

00:01:09.520 --> 00:01:11.590
to live with Adalines family in Meadsville

00:01:11.590 --> 00:01:14.320
Pennsylvania while his father

00:01:14.320 --> 00:01:16.930
William return to oil fields in Ohio.

00:01:16.930 --> 00:01:21.340
There his father meets and marrys Jeannie

00:01:21.340 --> 00:01:24.490
Dunlap on the sixteenth of April 1903

00:01:24.490 --> 00:01:28.180
The couple quickly reclaim young Clark

00:01:28.180 --> 00:01:31.390
and the family moved to Jenny's hometown

00:01:31.390 --> 00:01:35.469
Hopedale Ohio. Clark Gable will spend some

00:01:35.469 --> 00:01:37.689
of the happiest days of his life in

00:01:37.689 --> 00:01:41.350
Hopedale and in this house. He was

00:01:41.350 --> 00:01:44.380
pampered by step mother being an only

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:48.250
child she considered him as her own. She

00:01:48.250 --> 00:01:51.640
keep him clean and well-groomed. Clark

00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:53.679
was considered a good student and love

00:01:53.679 --> 00:01:56.710
music and the arts,  thanks to Jeannie.

00:01:56.710 --> 00:01:59.470
Now this is Clark showing off his

00:01:59.470 --> 00:02:02.470
musical talents as a youngster while

00:02:02.470 --> 00:02:06.760
playing in all adult band and this is

00:02:06.760 --> 00:02:11.080
clark at Hopewell Highschool in 1916. He's

00:02:11.080 --> 00:02:13.989
on the second row from the front and

00:02:13.989 --> 00:02:17.500
second from the right. The next year in

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:21.400
1917 the Clark family moved to this farm

00:02:21.400 --> 00:02:26.290
at 3150 Alliance Road. It's now county

00:02:26.290 --> 00:02:31.570
road 125 in Pelmier Ohio.  It's near

00:02:31.570 --> 00:02:34.810
Akron. He attended Edinburgh high school

00:02:34.810 --> 00:02:37.690
for a short time where he actually rode

00:02:37.690 --> 00:02:41.260
a horse to school and back each day. Clark

00:02:41.260 --> 00:02:45.040
soon grew tired of farm work. He quit

00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:49.330
school at age of 16, got a job in Akron

00:02:49.330 --> 00:02:52.300
at a rubber tire plant. Now this is the

00:02:52.300 --> 00:02:54.489
Miller tire company that Clark was

00:02:54.489 --> 00:02:58.269
working at when he visited the Akron

00:02:58.269 --> 00:03:01.600
music hall one afternoon after work to

00:03:01.600 --> 00:03:04.120
see the performance of The Bird of

00:03:04.120 --> 00:03:07.209
Paradise. Clark Gable knew immediately

00:03:07.209 --> 00:03:11.799
what he wanted to be. An actor. Acting

00:03:11.799 --> 00:03:13.930
was better than farming and factory work

00:03:13.930 --> 00:03:16.510
and he volunteered at the Playhouse

00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:19.000
doing whatever they wanted him to do

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:21.760
sweeping floors running errands he even

00:03:21.760 --> 00:03:25.870
had one walk-on part as an extra. His

00:03:25.870 --> 00:03:28.720
first taste of acting was cut short when

00:03:28.720 --> 00:03:31.239
he learned that Jenny, his stepmother, had

00:03:31.239 --> 00:03:33.880
died at their farm on January the 11th

00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:38.140
1920 of tuberculosis and cancer of the

00:03:38.140 --> 00:03:39.220
bowels.

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:43.900
Jenny is buried in the Palmar cemetery just

00:03:43.900 --> 00:03:46.600
down the road from their home.

00:03:46.600 --> 00:03:49.270
William Clark's name is on her tombstone

00:03:49.270 --> 00:03:53.020
but he's buried in California and died

00:03:53.020 --> 00:03:57.670
in 1948. Soon after Jeannys death William

00:03:57.670 --> 00:04:00.730
Clark moved to the oil fields of Oklahoma

00:04:00.730 --> 00:04:05.020
and Clark soon followed his dad. After

00:04:05.020 --> 00:04:08.380
two years of working in the oil fields

00:04:08.380 --> 00:04:11.560
he had saved enough money. Clark joined

00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:13.450
another theater group

00:04:13.450 --> 00:04:16.930
unfortunately the group soon went broke

00:04:16.930 --> 00:04:19.480
leaving Clark and others stranded in

00:04:19.480 --> 00:04:23.290
Butte Montana making his way finally to

00:04:23.290 --> 00:04:26.980
Oregan with a fellow actor and after working

00:04:26.980 --> 00:04:29.680
in several different jobs he managed to

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:32.919
join another theater group. There he

00:04:32.919 --> 00:04:36.460
meets Josephine Dylan, theatre manager

00:04:36.460 --> 00:04:39.520
and acting coach. She took a personal

00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:42.850
interest in Clark determined to make an

00:04:42.850 --> 00:04:46.630
actor out of Clark Gable. She paid to

00:04:46.630 --> 00:04:48.820
have his teeth fixed, filling in the

00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:52.810
front gaps. She had his hair styled and

00:04:52.810 --> 00:04:55.090
told him how to lower his high-pitched

00:04:55.090 --> 00:04:56.169
voice

00:04:56.169 --> 00:04:59.590
unfortunately, there's not much you can

00:04:59.590 --> 00:05:02.050
do about his large ears that stuck out.

00:05:02.050 --> 00:05:05.020
Now this proved to be the biggest

00:05:05.020 --> 00:05:07.360
obstacle to getting into the movie

00:05:07.360 --> 00:05:10.720
business. Years later his ears will be

00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:14.110
operated on and that will help some.

00:05:14.110 --> 00:05:17.229
Although Josephine was several years

00:05:17.229 --> 00:05:20.380
older than Clark the couple were married

00:05:20.380 --> 00:05:24.640
in December of 1924 and they'll move to

00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:28.150
Hollywood. Money will be tight and what

00:05:28.150 --> 00:05:31.030
extra there was from Josephine's acting

00:05:31.030 --> 00:05:34.240
classes will be spent on Clark trying to

00:05:34.240 --> 00:05:37.630
break into the movie business. For the

00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:40.780
next few years Gable will play extras in

00:05:40.780 --> 00:05:43.040
several silent films

00:05:43.040 --> 00:05:47.570
and in 1926 Clark and Josephine will

00:05:47.570 --> 00:05:51.080
separate. He will begin keeping company

00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:53.780
with wealthy women that he thought could

00:05:53.780 --> 00:05:57.080
further his career. For awhile he will

00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:59.660
leave Hollywood and try to return to the

00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:04.670
state. In 1930 Josephine will file

00:06:04.670 --> 00:06:07.820
for divorce on grounds of desertion. She

00:06:07.820 --> 00:06:10.250
will always say that Gable married his

00:06:10.250 --> 00:06:14.270
second wife Ria Lingham because Ria

00:06:14.270 --> 00:06:16.700
could do more for his career than she

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:20.780
could. Gables marriage to Josephine was

00:06:20.780 --> 00:06:21.980
strange.

00:06:21.980 --> 00:06:24.410
He always said that the marriage was

00:06:24.410 --> 00:06:27.440
never consummated and it was a marriage

00:06:27.440 --> 00:06:31.460
of convenience only, however, it will be the

00:06:31.460 --> 00:06:34.400
only marriage for Josephine and she'll

00:06:34.400 --> 00:06:38.630
always claim to love Clark. She soon

00:06:38.630 --> 00:06:41.540
fell on hard times after the divorce.

00:06:41.540 --> 00:06:45.320
A few years later she went to L.B. Mayer

00:06:45.320 --> 00:06:47.810
saying  Clark was not helping her

00:06:47.810 --> 00:06:50.510
financially and threatened to go to the

00:06:50.510 --> 00:06:53.750
newspapers. Mayor begin taking two

00:06:53.750 --> 00:06:56.840
hundred dollars out of Clark's pay to

00:06:56.840 --> 00:06:59.630
send to Josephine. It was later shown

00:06:59.630 --> 00:07:02.630
that Gable sent her money to keep her from

00:07:02.630 --> 00:07:05.540
foreclosure on her modest home.

00:07:05.540 --> 00:07:08.180
He also left provisions to pay of her

00:07:08.180 --> 00:07:13.310
mortgage.  41 years after her divorce from

00:07:13.310 --> 00:07:16.010
Clark Gable on the 11th of November

00:07:16.010 --> 00:07:22.130
1971, Josephine Dylan will die of a long

00:07:22.130 --> 00:07:25.580
time illness at a sanatorium in Glendale.

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:28.460
She'll be buried at the Calvary Cemetery

00:07:28.460 --> 00:07:33.830
in East Los Angeles. Josephine was 87

00:07:33.830 --> 00:07:37.820
years old.  While Clark was separated from

00:07:37.820 --> 00:07:38.320
Josephine in 1930 he met Maria Langham

00:07:38.320 --> 00:07:44.600
while in New York working back on

00:07:44.600 --> 00:07:48.500
the stage. Although Ria as she was called,

00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:52.070
was several years older than Gable,

00:07:52.070 --> 00:07:54.260
she was from a socially prominent

00:07:54.260 --> 00:07:54.760
wealthy Texas family

00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:58.479
and could afford to help his career

00:07:58.479 --> 00:08:01.539
back to where he really wanted to be in

00:08:01.539 --> 00:08:05.500
hollywood working on movies. They were

00:08:05.500 --> 00:08:09.430
married  April 3rd, 1931. Gable will

00:08:09.430 --> 00:08:12.430
be her fourth marriage and his second.

00:08:12.430 --> 00:08:15.970
While married to Ria Langham,  and with

00:08:15.970 --> 00:08:18.009
her help, he will become more

00:08:18.009 --> 00:08:21.789
sophisticated and polished. His movie

00:08:21.789 --> 00:08:24.250
career will begin to drastically improve.

00:08:24.250 --> 00:08:28.000
He will get his first speaking role in

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:31.870
The Painted Desert with William Boyd. Now

00:08:31.870 --> 00:08:34.570
this was before Boyd became Hopalong Cassidy.

00:08:34.570 --> 00:08:38.770
MGM will offer Clark a contract

00:08:38.770 --> 00:08:40.599
after seeing his performance in The

00:08:40.599 --> 00:08:43.419
Painted Desert. They will give him his

00:08:43.419 --> 00:08:46.870
first leading role in Dance Fools Dance

00:08:46.870 --> 00:08:51.640
with Joan Crawford. Clark Gable will be a

00:08:51.640 --> 00:08:55.270
leading man for the next 30 years.

00:08:55.270 --> 00:08:59.800
In 1932 he stars in Red Dust with Jean

00:08:59.800 --> 00:09:03.339
Harlow.  The next year he teams up again

00:09:03.339 --> 00:09:06.010
with Joan Crawford in Dancing Lady.

00:09:06.010 --> 00:09:09.610
Also, a young Fred Astaire will make his

00:09:09.610 --> 00:09:11.980
first dancing appearance on the screen

00:09:11.980 --> 00:09:15.279
During the filming of Dancing Lady

00:09:15.279 --> 00:09:19.450
Gable will become hospitalized with

00:09:19.450 --> 00:09:22.870
infected teeth. the infection will spread

00:09:22.870 --> 00:09:25.930
through his body causing him to have to

00:09:25.930 --> 00:09:29.080
have all of his teeth pulled.

00:09:29.080 --> 00:09:32.230
This caused delay in filming and cost

00:09:32.230 --> 00:09:33.710
the studio money.

00:09:33.710 --> 00:09:36.800
As punishment, Clark was rented out to

00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:39.620
the low-budget Columbia Pictures for a

00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:44.600
comedy called It Happened One Night. Gable

00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:46.640
thought the picture was awful he didn't

00:09:46.640 --> 00:09:47.900
like it.

00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:50.450
The picture was turned down by several

00:09:50.450 --> 00:09:52.850
actresses before Claudette Colbert

00:09:52.850 --> 00:09:57.470
agreed, at double her wages, to take it.

00:09:57.470 --> 00:10:00.890
Colbert and Gable both thought the little

00:10:00.890 --> 00:10:04.580
movie was stupid but the public loved it.

00:10:04.580 --> 00:10:08.510
It will be the only Academy Award

00:10:08.510 --> 00:10:13.070
Clark Gable will ever receive. The movie

00:10:13.070 --> 00:10:16.130
will recieve five Academy Awards putting

00:10:16.130 --> 00:10:18.770
Clark Gable back in the good graces of

00:10:18.770 --> 00:10:23.150
MGM executives. In the early part of 1935

00:10:23.150 --> 00:10:27.380
Gable will star with Loretta Young in

00:10:27.380 --> 00:10:30.170
The Call of the Wild. During the

00:10:30.170 --> 00:10:32.870
filming Loretta and Gable will become

00:10:32.870 --> 00:10:35.690
romantically involved, or at least that's

00:10:35.690 --> 00:10:38.810
what everyone thought. After filming

00:10:38.810 --> 00:10:40.610
Loretta will discovered that she's

00:10:40.610 --> 00:10:41.630
pregnant

00:10:41.630 --> 00:10:44.690
Both Loretta and Clark have morals

00:10:44.690 --> 00:10:48.080
clauses in their contracts and if the studio

00:10:48.080 --> 00:10:50.810
found out about her pregnancy they would

00:10:50.810 --> 00:10:54.950
both lose their contracts. Loretta took a

00:10:54.950 --> 00:10:58.370
long trip to Europe.  Judy, their daughter

00:10:58.370 --> 00:11:01.970
was born in November that year. Loretta

00:11:01.970 --> 00:11:04.430
went to great lengths to hide the fact

00:11:04.430 --> 00:11:07.370
that Judy was her own daughter. She

00:11:07.370 --> 00:11:10.190
claimed to have adopted Judy and it was

00:11:10.190 --> 00:11:12.140
years before Judy discovered that

00:11:12.140 --> 00:11:15.140
Loretta Young and Clark Gable were her

00:11:15.140 --> 00:11:16.850
natural parents.

00:11:16.850 --> 00:11:19.250
Clark Gable will never publicly

00:11:19.250 --> 00:11:23.630
acknowledged his daughter. In 1940, when

00:11:23.630 --> 00:11:25.370
Judy was four years old

00:11:25.370 --> 00:11:28.339
Loretta Young will marry producer Tom

00:11:28.339 --> 00:11:32.300
Lewis. Judy will take Lewis  last name.

00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:35.480
Tom and  Loretta will have two sons during

00:11:35.480 --> 00:11:36.529
their marriage.

00:11:36.529 --> 00:11:39.980
Christopher and Peter. Loretta and Tom

00:11:39.980 --> 00:11:40.480
will divorce in 1969 after a bitter battle.

00:11:40.480 --> 00:11:50.480
She will not marry again unti 1993 at the age of 80.

00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:54.050
She'll meet Gene Louis, a fashion

00:11:54.050 --> 00:11:57.589
designer that years earlier had designed

00:11:57.589 --> 00:11:59.870
her gowns for the Loretta Young show.

00:11:59.870 --> 00:12:05.269
They will remain married until his death four

00:12:05.269 --> 00:12:09.860
years later in 1997. That same year she

00:12:09.860 --> 00:12:13.759
married Gene Louis, Loretta will buy this

00:12:13.759 --> 00:12:19.160
house at 1075 Mantanna avenue in Palm

00:12:19.160 --> 00:12:22.399
Springs and live there until her death

00:12:22.399 --> 00:12:27.139
in 2004. Loretta Young will died of

